#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:4
msgid "Deprecations and Removals"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:6
msgid ""
"This page lists all pytest features that are currently deprecated or have "
"been removed in past major releases. The objective is to give users a clear "
"rationale why a certain feature has been removed, and what alternatives "
"should be used instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:16
msgid "Deprecated Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:18
msgid ""
"Below is a complete list of all pytest features which are considered "
"deprecated. Using those features will issue :class:`_pytest.warning_types."
"PytestWarning` or subclasses, which can be filtered using :ref:`standard "
"warning filters <warnings>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:24
msgid "``--no-print-logs`` command-line option"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:29
msgid ""
"Option ``--no-print-logs`` is deprecated and meant to be removed in a future "
"release. If you use ``--no-print-logs``, please try out ``--show-capture`` "
"and provide feedback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:32
msgid ""
"``--show-capture`` command-line option was added in ``pytest 3.5.0` and "
"allows to specify how to display captured output when tests fail: ``no``, "
"``stdout``, ``stderr``, ``log`` or ``all`` (the default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:38
msgid "Node Construction changed to ``Node.from_parent``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:42
msgid ""
"The construction of nodes new should use the named constructor "
"``from_parent``. This limitation in api surface intends to enable better/"
"simpler refactoring of the collection tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:47
msgid "``junit_family`` default value change to \"xunit2\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:51
msgid ""
"The default value of ``junit_family`` option will change to ``xunit2`` in "
"pytest 6.0, given that this is the version supported by default in modern "
"tools that manipulate this type of file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:54
msgid ""
"In order to smooth the transition, pytest will issue a warning in case the "
"``--junitxml`` option is given in the command line but ``junit_family`` is "
"not explicitly configured in ``pytest.ini``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:57
msgid ""
"PytestDeprecationWarning: The 'junit_family' default value will change to "
"'xunit2' in pytest 6.0.\n"
"  Add 'junit_family=legacy' to your pytest.ini file to silence this warning "
"and make your suite compatible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:60
msgid ""
"In order to silence this warning, users just need to configure the "
"``junit_family`` option explicitly:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:62
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"junit_family=legacy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:69
msgid "``funcargnames`` alias for ``fixturenames``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:73
msgid ""
"The ``FixtureRequest``, ``Metafunc``, and ``Function`` classes track the "
"names of their associated fixtures, with the aptly-named ``fixturenames`` "
"attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:76
msgid ""
"Prior to pytest 2.3, this attribute was named ``funcargnames``, and we have "
"kept that as an alias since.  It is finally due for removal, as it is often "
"confusing in places where we or plugin authors must distinguish between "
"fixture names and names supplied by non-fixture things such as ``pytest.mark."
"parametrize``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:83
msgid "Result log (``--result-log``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:87
msgid ""
"The ``--result-log`` option produces a stream of test reports which can be "
"analysed at runtime, but it uses a custom format which requires users to "
"implement their own parser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:91
msgid ""
"The  `pytest-reportlog <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest-reportlog>`__ "
"plugin provides a ``--report-log`` option, a more standard and extensible "
"alternative, producing one JSON object per-line, and should cover the same "
"use cases. Please try it out and provide feedback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:94
msgid ""
"The plan is remove the ``--result-log`` option in pytest 6.0 if ``pytest-"
"reportlog`` proves satisfactory to all users and is deemed stable. The "
"``pytest-reportlog`` plugin might even be merged into the core at some "
"point, depending on the plans for the plugins and number of users using it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:99
msgid "TerminalReporter.writer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:103
msgid ""
"The ``TerminalReporter.writer`` attribute has been deprecated and should no "
"longer be used. This was inadvertently exposed as part of the public API of "
"that plugin and ties it too much with ``py.io.TerminalWriter``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:107
msgid ""
"Plugins that used ``TerminalReporter.writer`` directly should instead use "
"``TerminalReporter`` methods that provide the same functionality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:112
msgid "Removed Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:114
msgid ""
"As stated in our :ref:`backwards-compatibility` policy, deprecated features "
"are removed only in major releases after an appropriate period of "
"deprecation has passed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:119
msgid "``pytest.config`` global"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:123
msgid ""
"The ``pytest.config`` global object is deprecated.  Instead use ``request."
"config`` (via the ``request`` fixture) or if you are a plugin author use the "
"``pytest_configure(config)`` hook. Note that many hooks can also access the "
"``config`` object indirectly, through ``session.config`` or ``item.config`` "
"for example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:132
msgid "``\"message\"`` parameter of ``pytest.raises``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:136
msgid ""
"It is a common mistake to think this parameter will match the exception "
"message, while in fact it only serves to provide a custom message in case "
"the ``pytest.raises`` check fails. To prevent users from making this "
"mistake, and because it is believed to be little used, pytest is deprecating "
"it without providing an alternative for the moment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:141
msgid ""
"If you have a valid use case for this parameter, consider that to obtain the "
"same results you can just call ``pytest.fail`` manually at the end of the "
"``with`` statement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:144 ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:439
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:146
msgid ""
"with pytest.raises(TimeoutError, message=\"Client got unexpected "
"message\"):\n"
"    wait_for(websocket.recv(), 0.5)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:152 ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:185
#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:310 ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:374
msgid "Becomes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:154
msgid ""
"with pytest.raises(TimeoutError):\n"
"    wait_for(websocket.recv(), 0.5)\n"
"    pytest.fail(\"Client got unexpected message\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:161
msgid ""
"If you still have concerns about this deprecation and future removal, please "
"comment on `issue #3974 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/"
"issues/3974>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:168
msgid "``raises`` / ``warns`` with a string as the second argument"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:172
msgid ""
"Use the context manager form of these instead.  When necessary, invoke "
"``exec`` directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:175 ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:302
#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:325
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "範例："

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:177
msgid ""
"pytest.raises(ZeroDivisionError, \"1 / 0\")\n"
"pytest.raises(SyntaxError, \"a $ b\")\n"
"\n"
"pytest.warns(DeprecationWarning, \"my_function()\")\n"
"pytest.warns(SyntaxWarning, \"assert(1, 2)\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:187
msgid ""
"with pytest.raises(ZeroDivisionError):\n"
"    1 / 0\n"
"with pytest.raises(SyntaxError):\n"
"    exec(\"a $ b\")  # exec is required for invalid syntax\n"
"\n"
"with pytest.warns(DeprecationWarning):\n"
"    my_function()\n"
"with pytest.warns(SyntaxWarning):\n"
"    exec(\"assert(1, 2)\")  # exec is used to avoid a top-level warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:203
msgid "Using ``Class`` in custom Collectors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:207
msgid ""
"Using objects named ``\"Class\"`` as a way to customize the type of nodes "
"that are collected in ``Collector`` subclasses has been deprecated. Users "
"instead should use ``pytest_pycollect_makeitem`` to customize node types "
"during collection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:211
msgid ""
"This issue should affect only advanced plugins who create new collection "
"types, so if you see this warning message please contact the authors so they "
"can change the code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:216
msgid "marks in ``pytest.mark.parametrize``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:220
msgid ""
"Applying marks to values of a ``pytest.mark.parametrize`` call is now "
"deprecated. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:222
msgid ""
"@pytest.mark.parametrize(\n"
"    \"a, b\",\n"
"    [\n"
"        (3, 9),\n"
"        pytest.mark.xfail(reason=\"flaky\")(6, 36),\n"
"        (10, 100),\n"
"        (20, 200),\n"
"        (40, 400),\n"
"        (50, 500),\n"
"    ],\n"
")\n"
"def test_foo(a, b):\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:238
msgid ""
"This code applies the ``pytest.mark.xfail(reason=\"flaky\")`` mark to the "
"``(6, 36)`` value of the above parametrization call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:241
msgid ""
"This was considered hard to read and understand, and also its implementation "
"presented problems to the code preventing further internal improvements in "
"the marks architecture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:244
msgid "To update the code, use ``pytest.param``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:246
msgid ""
"@pytest.mark.parametrize(\n"
"    \"a, b\",\n"
"    [\n"
"        (3, 9),\n"
"        pytest.param(6, 36, marks=pytest.mark.xfail(reason=\"flaky\")),\n"
"        (10, 100),\n"
"        (20, 200),\n"
"        (40, 400),\n"
"        (50, 500),\n"
"    ],\n"
")\n"
"def test_foo(a, b):\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:264
msgid "``pytest_funcarg__`` prefix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:268
msgid ""
"In very early pytest versions fixtures could be defined using the "
"``pytest_funcarg__`` prefix:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:270
msgid ""
"def pytest_funcarg__data():\n"
"    return SomeData()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:275
msgid "Switch over to the ``@pytest.fixture`` decorator:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:277
msgid ""
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def data():\n"
"    return SomeData()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:286
msgid "[pytest] section in setup.cfg files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:290
msgid ""
"``[pytest]`` sections in ``setup.cfg`` files should now be named ``[tool:"
"pytest]`` to avoid conflicts with other distutils commands."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:295
msgid "Metafunc.addcall"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:299
msgid ""
":meth:`_pytest.python.Metafunc.addcall` was a precursor to the current "
"parametrized mechanism. Users should use :meth:`_pytest.python.Metafunc."
"parametrize` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:304
msgid ""
"def pytest_generate_tests(metafunc):\n"
"    metafunc.addcall({\"i\": 1}, id=\"1\")\n"
"    metafunc.addcall({\"i\": 2}, id=\"2\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:312
msgid ""
"def pytest_generate_tests(metafunc):\n"
"    metafunc.parametrize(\"i\", [1, 2], ids=[\"1\", \"2\"])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:319
msgid "``cached_setup``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:323
msgid ""
"``request.cached_setup`` was the precursor of the setup/teardown mechanism "
"available to fixtures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:327
msgid ""
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def db_session():\n"
"    return request.cached_setup(\n"
"        setup=Session.create, teardown=lambda session: session.close(), "
"scope=\"module\"\n"
"    )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:335
msgid "This should be updated to make use of standard fixture mechanisms:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:337
msgid ""
"@pytest.fixture(scope=\"module\")\n"
"def db_session():\n"
"    session = Session.create()\n"
"    yield session\n"
"    session.close()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:346
msgid ""
"You can consult `funcarg comparison section in the docs <https://docs.pytest."
"org/en/latest/funcarg_compare.html>`_ for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:351
msgid "pytest_plugins in non-top-level conftest files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:355
msgid ""
"Defining ``pytest_plugins`` is now deprecated in non-top-level conftest.py "
"files because they will activate referenced plugins *globally*, which is "
"surprising because for all other pytest features ``conftest.py`` files are "
"only *active* for tests at or below it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:361
msgid "``Config.warn`` and ``Node.warn``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:365
msgid ""
"Those methods were part of the internal pytest warnings system, but since "
"``3.8`` pytest is using the builtin warning system for its own warnings, so "
"those two functions are now deprecated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:368
msgid ""
"``Config.warn`` should be replaced by calls to the standard ``warnings."
"warn``, example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:370
msgid "config.warn(\"C1\", \"some warning\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:376
msgid "warnings.warn(pytest.PytestWarning(\"some warning\"))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:380
msgid "``Node.warn`` now supports two signatures:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:382
msgid ""
"``node.warn(PytestWarning(\"some message\"))``: is now the **recommended** "
"way to call this function. The warning instance must be a PytestWarning or "
"subclass."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:385
msgid ""
"``node.warn(\"CI\", \"some message\")``: this code/message form has been "
"**removed** and should be converted to the warning instance form above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:388
msgid "record_xml_property"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:392
msgid ""
"The ``record_xml_property`` fixture is now deprecated in favor of the more "
"generic ``record_property``, which can be used by other consumers (for "
"example ``pytest-html``) to obtain custom information about the test run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:395
msgid "This is just a matter of renaming the fixture as the API is the same:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:397
msgid ""
"def test_foo(record_xml_property):\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:402
msgid "Change to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:404
msgid ""
"def test_foo(record_property):\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:411
msgid "Passing command-line string to ``pytest.main()``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:415
msgid "Passing a command-line string to ``pytest.main()`` is deprecated:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:417
msgid "pytest.main(\"-v -s\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:421
msgid "Pass a list instead:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:423
msgid "pytest.main([\"-v\", \"-s\"])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:428
msgid ""
"By passing a string, users expect that pytest will interpret that command-"
"line using the shell rules they are working on (for example ``bash`` or "
"``Powershell``), but this is very hard/impossible to do in a portable way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:433
msgid "Calling fixtures directly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:437
msgid ""
"Calling a fixture function directly, as opposed to request them in a test "
"function, is deprecated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:441
msgid ""
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def cell():\n"
"    return ...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def full_cell():\n"
"    cell = cell()\n"
"    cell.make_full()\n"
"    return cell"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:454
msgid ""
"This is a great source of confusion to new users, which will often call the "
"fixture functions and request them from test functions interchangeably, "
"which breaks the fixture resolution model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:456
msgid ""
"In those cases just request the function directly in the dependent fixture:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:458
msgid ""
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def cell():\n"
"    return ...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def full_cell(cell):\n"
"    cell.make_full()\n"
"    return cell"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:470
msgid ""
"Alternatively if the fixture function is called multiple times inside a test "
"(making it hard to apply the above pattern) or if you would like to make "
"minimal changes to the code, you can create a fixture which calls the "
"original function together with the ``name`` parameter:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:474
msgid ""
"def cell():\n"
"    return ...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.fixture(name=\"cell\")\n"
"def cell_fixture():\n"
"    return cell()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:486
msgid "``yield`` tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:490
msgid ""
"pytest supported ``yield``-style tests, where a test function actually "
"``yield`` functions and values that are then turned into proper test "
"methods. Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:493
msgid ""
"def check(x, y):\n"
"    assert x ** x == y\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def test_squared():\n"
"    yield check, 2, 4\n"
"    yield check, 3, 9"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:503
msgid "This would result into two actual test functions being generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:505
msgid ""
"This form of test function doesn't support fixtures properly, and users "
"should switch to ``pytest.mark.parametrize``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:507
msgid ""
"@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"x, y\", [(2, 4), (3, 9)])\n"
"def test_squared(x, y):\n"
"    assert x ** x == y"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:514
msgid "Internal classes accessed through ``Node``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:518
msgid ""
"Access of ``Module``, ``Function``, ``Class``, ``Instance``, ``File`` and "
"``Item`` through ``Node`` instances now issue this warning:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:521
msgid ""
"usage of Function.Module is deprecated, please use pytest.Module instead"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:525
msgid ""
"Users should just ``import pytest`` and access those objects using the "
"``pytest`` module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:527
msgid ""
"This has been documented as deprecated for years, but only now we are "
"actually emitting deprecation warnings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:530
msgid "``Node.get_marker``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:534
msgid ""
"As part of a large :ref:`marker-revamp`, :meth:`_pytest.nodes.Node."
"get_marker` is deprecated. See :ref:`the documentation <update marker code>` "
"on tips on how to update your code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:539
msgid "``somefunction.markname``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:543
msgid ""
"As part of a large :ref:`marker-revamp` we already deprecated using "
"``MarkInfo`` the only correct way to get markers of an element is via ``node."
"iter_markers(name)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:548
msgid "``pytest_namespace``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:552
msgid ""
"This hook is deprecated because it greatly complicates the pytest internals "
"regarding configuration and initialization, making some bug fixes and "
"refactorings impossible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:555
msgid "Example of usage:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:557
msgid ""
"class MySymbol:\n"
"    ...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def pytest_namespace():\n"
"    return {\"my_symbol\": MySymbol()}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:567
msgid ""
"Plugin authors relying on this hook should instead require that users now "
"import the plugin modules directly (with an appropriate public API)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:569
msgid ""
"As a stopgap measure, plugin authors may still inject their names into "
"pytest's namespace, usually during ``pytest_configure``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:571
msgid ""
"import pytest\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def pytest_configure():\n"
"    pytest.my_symbol = MySymbol()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:583
msgid "Reinterpretation mode (``--assert=reinterp``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:587
msgid ""
"Reinterpretation mode has now been removed and only plain and rewrite mode "
"are available, consequently the ``--assert=reinterp`` option is no longer "
"available.  This also means files imported from plugins or ``conftest.py`` "
"will not benefit from improved assertions by default, you should use "
"``pytest.register_assert_rewrite()`` to explicitly turn on assertion "
"rewriting for those files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/deprecations.rst:595
msgid "Removed command-line options"
msgstr ""

